"Heather Remind Me"]

30:09.000 --> 30:11.208
♪ Heather I'm on a plane ♪

30:11.208 --> 30:15.083
♪ That I pray
won't get off the ground ♪

30:17.291 --> 30:20.084
♪ It's a perfectly clear day ♪

30:20.084 --> 30:24.041
♪ But I've got storm clouds
in my mind ♪

30:25.625 --> 30:29.041
♪ So foolish why I do this ♪

30:29.041 --> 30:32.417
♪ Why I'd do it all again ♪

30:34.959 --> 30:39.708
♪ Heather remind me
how this ends ♪

30:41.083 --> 30:44.208
♪ Give me a few days ♪

30:44.208 --> 30:48.209
♪ And I'll be feeling fine ♪

30:50.000 --> 30:52.041
♪ I can't stop moving ♪

30:52.041 --> 30:56.792
♪ I move backwards in time.. ♪

30:57.834 --> 30:59.000
Jake.

30:59.000 --> 31:00.375
♪ To where I left you ♪

31:00.375 --> 31:04.208
♪ It was so good
we both pretend.. ♪

31:04.208 --> 31:07.209
- How'd you find me?
- Where else would you be?

31:07.209 --> 31:08.959
♪ Heather remind me ♪

31:08.959 --> 31:12.208
♪ How this ends ♪

31:12.208 --> 31:16.583
Marti's deal is a good one,
better than you deserve.

31:16.583 --> 31:18.042
Others did worse.

31:18.042 --> 31:20.208
What's that got to do
with anything?

31:20.208 --> 31:22.125
The bad guys
manipulate the system.

31:22.125 --> 31:24.291
They know how to win.
That doesn't make them right.

31:24.291 --> 31:26.000
If you're the only one
playin' by the rules

31:26.000 --> 31:27.417
that makes you a sucker.

31:27.417 --> 31:29.125
Forget about them.

31:29.125 --> 31:31.500
They're gonna have
to live with their mistakes.

31:31.500 --> 31:33.208
This is about you.

31:35.959 --> 31:37.583
You know I'm not an idiot.

31:39.333 --> 31:41.000
[sighing]

31:41.000 --> 31:45.125
It's all over your face,
I'm...disappointin' you.

31:46.209 --> 31:48.167
And it kills me..

31:49.166 --> 31:51.583
...but I can't go to jail.

31:53.125 --> 31:54.250
I just can't.

31:54.250 --> 31:56.208
You're a first-time offender
making

31:56.208 --> 32:01.166
a, a big dramatic confession
to save an honest man.

32:03.084 --> 32:05.167
That's gonna play well.

32:06.625 --> 32:10.667
- You'll do easy time.
- It's prison, Alice.

32:10.667 --> 32:15.042
I wouldn't last.
I'm not strong enough
for that.

32:18.834 --> 32:21.000
I'm gonna go away somewhere.

32:22.708 --> 32:24.125
I can't be here.

32:29.084 --> 32:32.250
I'm sorry, Alice.
I wish I was a better guy.

32:38.041 --> 32:41.792
Do you believe in God?

32:41.792 --> 32:43.209
Of course, I believe in God.

32:43.209 --> 32:45.375
Do you think He has a hand
in the things we do?

32:45.375 --> 32:48.458
- Where is this goin'?
- Answer the question.

32:49.792 --> 32:52.375
Sure. Yes, I do.

32:52.375 --> 32:56.417
Look at how perfectly
everything lines up.

32:56.417 --> 32:59.125
Marti moves in to Cheertown.
I start dating you.

32:59.125 --> 33:01.542
Marti's law case connects
to the pharmacy you robbed.

33:01.542 --> 33:06.166
What if God knew
a great injustice
had happened?

33:06.166 --> 33:08.167
'An innocent man
was suffering'

33:08.167 --> 33:11.208
and something
needed to be done?

33:11.208 --> 33:14.167
God's not gonna...
do something flashy

33:14.167 --> 33:17.042
like sending out a plague
of locusts, right?

33:18.209 --> 33:20.458
'He's gonna work
under the radar.'

33:26.917 --> 33:29.250
Since when are you religious,
anyway?

33:29.250 --> 33:31.166
Just because I don't talk
about it doesn't mean

33:31.166 --> 33:33.167
it's not important to me.

33:36.000 --> 33:39.209
But you can believe
whatever you want.

33:43.125 --> 33:45.208
It's your life.

34:01.000 --> 34:03.084
Would you visit me?

34:04.084 --> 34:05.167
[sighing]

34:05.167 --> 34:07.000
[instrumental music]

34:11.625 --> 34:14.667
As often as you'd like.

34:14.667 --> 34:18.083
And I will stand by
your side when you
make the announcement.

34:24.333 --> 34:26.166
That would help.

34:34.000 --> 34:36.417
You maybe wanna pray with me?

34:42.000 --> 34:43.708
Sure.

34:45.375 --> 34:47.542
We should, um..

34:47.542 --> 34:51.042
...we should do it silently.

34:51.042 --> 34:53.083
Means more that way.

34:57.166 --> 34:59.167
Okay.

35:09.750 --> 35:12.500
[music continues]

35:27.542 --> 35:28.667
[guitar music]

35:28.667 --> 35:30.250
(Jake)
Thank you all for comin'.

35:30.250 --> 35:32.708
This is difficult for me.

35:32.708 --> 35:36.333
I'm afraid
I've let all of you down

35:36.333 --> 35:40.084
my friends, teammates..

35:40.084 --> 35:42.750
...coaches and our fans.

35:44.458 --> 35:48.333
I know now that
an innocent man went
to jail for my crime.

35:50.083 --> 35:52.333
I can't allow that
to continue.

35:54.583 --> 35:57.083
And that's why
I've come forward

35:57.083 --> 35:59.209
and told the district attorney

35:59.209 --> 36:03.042
that Travis Guthrie
must go free.

36:05.000 --> 36:07.500
And I must do my time.

36:08.750 --> 36:11.125
[crowd applauding]

36:22.834 --> 36:25.291
- They love me.
- See?

36:25.291 --> 36:28.792
Told you it would play well.
Now go meet your fans.

36:32.542 --> 36:34.542
Local football hero,
Jake Harrow

36:34.542 --> 36:38.083
has just put it all on
the line in order
to do the right thing.

36:38.083 --> 36:40.083
John, in a world
where we can assume

36:40.083 --> 36:42.125
anyone forced in front
of the cameras is lying

36:42.125 --> 36:45.000
his honesty
was a breath of fresh air.

36:45.000 --> 36:47.500
There was a lot of emotions as
Harrow came clean to his fans.

36:47.500 --> 36:49.583
In fact, several had
tears in their eyes

36:49.583 --> 36:51.500
'as he took responsibility
for his actions.'

36:51.500 --> 36:54.667
